<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-08T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-08T07:00:00-05:00" n="332" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d332">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/106</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-08T12:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1917, 12 noon</hi></date>. <lb/>
                                    [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>819. Department’s 697, October 5, 5 p.m., concerning British-Spanish
                            agreement fuel and iron ore. British Ambassador handed me today
                            memorandum in which appears following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>The British Government understands that unless supplies reach
                                    Spain shortly, the position of the present Government, which is
                                    friendly, may be seriously affected, owing to the urgent need of
                                    coal.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>